14. E medio. ‘⁴ From amongst you.” This I conceive to be the author’s meaning. Donatus doubts whether he meant e vita or ex urbe. -- Nos jam fabula sumus. “ We are now become a loy-word, The old man and the old woman.'’ Donatus imagines this to allude to the ancient manner of writing in rables, which very often began in these words, ’γέρων καὶ γραῦς, senex atque anus. Thus in Plautus we meet with one who begins a story in these words: Fuit olim, quasi ego sum, senex. See Muretus', Var. Lect. xviii. 18, p. 468. Schirach (θίαν. ·Poet.
